      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"adaptation_kind\":\"Restructure\",\"safety_tier\":\"Green\",\"nudge_patch\":null,\"restructure_plan\":{\"revised_weekly_targets\":[{\"week_number\":1,\"weekly_target_km\":30},{\"week_number\":2,\"weekly_target_km\":34},{\"week_number\":3,\"weekly_target_km\":38}],\"revised_current_week_workouts\":[{\"day_of_week\":1,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":7,\"target_duration_minutes\":42,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start slow, let the body warm up gradually.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":32,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Conversational effort throughout. No surges.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Wind down the pace and walk the final minute if needed.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"5 minutes very easy jogging before settling into pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Finish with gentle walking and light leg stretches.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Monday stays unchanged. This is the base for the week. Keep the effort genuinely easy.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":6,\"target_duration_minutes\":36,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Ease in gently. No effort required here.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":26,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Hold a comfortable, conversational pace. Stop if legs still feel flat.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Slow to a walk for the final minute.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Walk 2 minutes, then ease into a jog before starting the easy segment.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Light stretching focusing on quads and calves.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"The Tempo session is replaced with an easy run this week. The legs need aerobic work without intensity stress while fatigue clears.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"workout_type\":\"Recovery\",\"title\":\"Recovery Run\",\"target_distance_km\":5,\"target_duration_minutes\":35,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":375,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":375,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":35,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Very relaxed. If legs still feel heavy, shorten to 4 km without concern.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Begin with a brisk 2 minute walk.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk 3 minutes and stretch lightly.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Shortened from 6 km to 5 km. Recovery pace is intentionally slower than easy pace. The goal is blood flow, not load.\",\"perceived_effort\":3},{\"day_of_week\":0,\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"title\":\"Long Run\",\"target_distance_km\":12,\"target_duration_minutes\":72,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Start conservatively. First 2 km should feel effortless.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":62,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Steady aerobic effort throughout. If legs feel flat again, cut to 10 km without guilt.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Slow the last 5 minutes. Walk the final minute.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Walk 2 minutes before starting. Ease into the run across the first kilometre.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk and stretch for 5 to 10 minutes after finishing.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Long run reduced from 14 km to 12 km. This restores a manageable long run that builds confidence rather than compounds fatigue. Complete it at easy effort only.\",\"perceived_effort\":5}],\"forward_path\":\"Week 2 target is set at 34 km, recovering from the adjusted 30 km week. The Tempo session returns in Week 2 at its prescribed pace zone once the easy runs this week feel controlled and the legs respond. Week 3 builds to 38 km, and if progression holds through Weeks 2 and 3, the plan rejoins the original meso targets by Week 4. The sub-1:45 goal remains achievable. A two-week consolidation at slightly reduced volume costs nothing in fitness compared to the risk of compounding fatigue into the build phase.\"},\"net_load_delta\":-9,\"rationale\":\"Three consecutive sessions showed accumulated fatigue, not a one-off off-day. Wednesday Tempo came in 45 seconds per km slower than the prescribed threshold band. Friday Easy ran 18 percent longer than the target duration at the same distance, signalling slower leg turnover. Sunday Long Run was cut by 5 km with reported leg heaviness and no power output despite adequate breathing, which points to muscular fatigue rather than a cardiovascular limit. The pattern across all three sessions is consistent: the body is carrying more residual load than the plan assumed. The changes for this week are: Wednesday Tempo is replaced with an easy 6 km run, Friday is reduced from 6 km to a 5 km recovery run at a relaxed pace, and Sunday Long Run is brought back to 12 km at easy effort. Monday stays as planned. The week total adjusts to 30 km. This gives the legs a genuine reset while keeping aerobic continuity. Weeks 2 and 3 step back up gradually through 34 km and 38 km, returning the Tempo session in Week 2 once the easy runs this week feel controlled. The sub-1:45 goal is built over 16 weeks. A short consolidation block now protects the quality of every session that follows.\",\"referral_category\":null}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
